<item>
            <title>[HBASE-4294] HLogSplitter sleeps with 1-second granularity</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4294</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The HLogSplitter writer threads wait in 1-second intervals for data. When data arrives, notify() is called and they wake up. But when the main thread needs to notify the writers to shut down, it doesn&apos;t notify. Hence, the writers always wait up to a full extra second for each log split.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
